 :mailbomb: (also mail bomb) [USENET] 1. v. To send, or urge others to send,
massive amounts of {email} to a single system or person, esp. with intent to
crash or {spam} the recipient's system. Sometimes done in retaliation for a
perceived serious offense. Mailbombing is itself widely regarded as a serious
offense -- it can disrupt email traffic or other facilities for innocent
users on the victim's system, and in extreme cases, even at upstream sites.
2. n. An automatic procedure with a similar effect. 3. n. The mail sent.
Compare {letterbomb}, {nastygram}.